  <Name>k__BackingField: Philippians
  fancyName: 
  nickname: php
  language: English
  lang: eng
  version: New Living Translation
  ver: NLT
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: "This letter is from Paul and Timothy, slaves of Christ Jesus.\n\tI
        am writing to all of God\u2019s holy people in Philippi who belong to Christ
        Jesus, including the church leaders[COMMENT[0]] and deacons.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: 'overseers, '
        - ft: 'or '
          body: bishops.
    - title: 
      content: 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you grace and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Thanksgiving and Prayer"
      content: 'Every time I think of you, I give thanks to my God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Whenever I pray, I make my requests for all of you with joy, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'for you have been my partners in spreading the Good News about Christ
        from the time you first heard it until now. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I am certain that God, who began the good work within you, will
        continue his work until it is finally finished on the day when Christ Jesus
        returns.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So it is right that I should feel as I do about all of you, for you
        have a special place in my heart. You share with me the special favor of
        God, both in my imprisonment and in defending and confirming the truth of
        the Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God knows how much I love you and long for you with the tender compassion
        of Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I pray that your love will overflow more and more, and that you will
        keep on growing in knowledge and understanding. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I want you to understand what really matters, so that you may
        live pure and blameless lives until the day of Christ\u2019s return. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "May you always be filled with the fruit of your salvation\u2014the
        righteous character produced in your life by Jesus Christ[COMMENT[0]]\u2014for
        this will bring much glory and praise to God.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: with the fruit of righteousness through Jesus Christ.
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Joy That Christ Is Preached"
      content: 'And I want you to know, my dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]]
        that everything that has happened to me here has helped to spread the Good
        News. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: brothers.
    - title: 
      content: 'For everyone here, including the whole palace guard,[COMMENT[0]]
        knows that I am in chains because of Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: including all the Praetorium.
    - title: 
      content: "And because of my imprisonment, most of the believers[COMMENT[0]]
        here have gained confidence and boldly speak God\u2019s message[COMMENT[1]]
        without fear.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: brothers in the Lord.
      - number: '1:14b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: speak the message.
    - title: 
      content: "It\u2019s true that some are preaching out of jealousy and rivalry.
        But others preach about Christ with pure motives. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They preach because they love me, for they know I have been appointed
        to defend the Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those others do not have pure motives as they preach about Christ.
        They preach with selfish ambition, not sincerely, intending to make my chains
        more painful to me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But that doesn\u2019t matter. Whether their motives are false or
        genuine, the message about Christ is being preached either way, so I rejoice.
        And I will continue to rejoice. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I know that as you pray for me and the Spirit of Jesus Christ
        helps me, this will lead to my deliverance.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Life for Christ"
      content: 'For I fully expect and hope that I will never be ashamed, but that
        I will continue to be bold for Christ, as I have been in the past. And I
        trust that my life will bring honor to Christ, whether I live or die. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For to me, living means living for Christ, and dying is even better. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But if I live, I can do more fruitful work for Christ. So I really
        don\u2019t know which is better. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019m torn between two desires: I long to go and be with Christ,
        which would be far better for me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But for your sakes, it is better that I continue to live.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Knowing this, I am convinced that I will remain alive so I can continue
        to help all of you grow and experience the joy of your faith. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And when I come to you again, you will have even more reason to take
        pride in Christ Jesus because of what he is doing through me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Live as Citizens of Heaven
      content: 'Above all, you must live as citizens of heaven, conducting yourselves
        in a manner worthy of the Good News about Christ. Then, whether I come and
        see you again or only hear about you, I will know that you are standing together
        with one spirit and one purpose, fighting together for the faith, which is
        the Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be intimidated in any way by your enemies. This will be
        a sign to them that they are going to be destroyed, but that you are going
        to be saved, even by God himself. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For you have been given not only the privilege of trusting in Christ
        but also the privilege of suffering for him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: We are in this struggle together. You have seen my struggle in the
        past, and you know that I am still in the midst of it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Have the Attitude of Christ
      content: 'Is there any encouragement from belonging to Christ? Any comfort
        from his love? Any fellowship together in the Spirit? Are your hearts tender
        and compassionate? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then make me truly happy by agreeing wholeheartedly with each other,
        loving one another, and working together with one mind and purpose.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t be selfish; don\u2019t try to impress others. Be humble,
        thinking of others as better than yourselves. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t look out only for your own interests, but take an interest
        in others, too.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You must have the same attitude that Christ Jesus had.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Though he was God,[COMMENT[0]]he did not think of equality with God\n\tas
        something to cling to.  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:6 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: Being in the form of God.
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, he gave up his divine privileges[COMMENT[0]];\n\the took
        the humble position of a slave[COMMENT[1]]and was born as a human being.\n\tWhen
        he appeared in human form,[COMMENT[2]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:7a '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: he emptied himself.
      - number: '2:7b '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: the form of a slave.
      - number: '2:7c '
        contents:
        - ft: Some English translations put this phrase in verse 8.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "he humbled himself in obedience to God\n\tand died a criminal\u2019s
        death on a cross.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, God elevated him to the place of highest honor\n\tand
        gave him the name above all other names,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "that at the name of Jesus every knee should bow,\n\tin heaven and
        on earth and under the earth,  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and every tongue declare that Jesus Christ is Lord,\n\tto the glory
        of God the Father.  "
      comments: []
    - title: Shine Brightly for Christ
      content: 'Dear friends, you always followed my instructions when I was with
        you. And now that I am away, it is even more important. Work hard to show
        the results of your salvation, obeying God with deep reverence and fear. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For God is working in you, giving you the desire and the power to
        do what pleases him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Do everything without complaining and arguing, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so that no one can criticize you. Live clean, innocent lives as children
        of God, shining like bright lights in a world full of crooked and perverse
        people. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Hold firmly to the word of life; then, on the day of Christ\u2019s
        return, I will be proud that I did not run the race in vain and that my work
        was not useless. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will rejoice even if I lose my life, pouring it out like a
        liquid offering to God,[COMMENT[0]] just like your faithful service is an
        offering to God. And I want all of you to share that joy. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: I will rejoice even if I am to be poured out as a liquid offering.
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, you should rejoice, and I will share your joy.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Paul Commends Timothy
      content: 'If the Lord Jesus is willing, I hope to send Timothy to you soon
        for a visit. Then he can cheer me up by telling me how you are getting along. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have no one else like Timothy, who genuinely cares about your welfare. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All the others care only for themselves and not for what matters
        to Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But you know how Timothy has proved himself. Like a son with his
        father, he has served with me in preaching the Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I hope to send him to you just as soon as I find out what is going
        to happen to me here. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I have confidence from the Lord that I myself will come to see
        you soon.  '
      comments: []
    - title: Paul Commends Epaphroditus
      content: 'Meanwhile, I thought I should send Epaphroditus back to you. He is
        a true brother, co-worker, and fellow soldier. And he was your messenger
        to help me in my need. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am sending him because he has been longing to see you, and he was
        very distressed that you heard he was ill. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And he certainly was ill; in fact, he almost died. But God had mercy
        on him\u2014and also on me, so that I would not have one sorrow after another.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I am all the more anxious to send him back to you, for I know
        you will be glad to see him, and then I will not be so worried about you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Welcome him in the Lord\u2019s love[COMMENT[0]] and with great joy,
        and give him the honor that people like him deserve. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:29 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: in the Lord.
    - title: 
      content: "For he risked his life for the work of Christ, and he was at the
        point of death while doing for me what you couldn\u2019t do from far away."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: The Priceless Value of Knowing Christ
      content: 'Whatever happens, my dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]] rejoice
        in the Lord. I never get tired of telling you these things, and I do it to
        safeguard your faith.  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'brothers; '
        - ft: also in 3:13, 17.
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: 'Watch out for those dogs, those people who do evil, those mutilators
        who say you must be circumcised to be saved. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we who worship by the Spirit of God[COMMENT[0]] are the ones
        who are truly circumcised. We rely on what Christ Jesus has done for us.
        We put no confidence in human effort, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: 'worship God in spirit; '
        - ft: 'one early manuscript reads '
          body: worship in spirit.
    - title: 
      content: 'though I could have confidence in my own effort if anyone could.
        Indeed, if others have reason for confidence in their own efforts, I have
        even more!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I was circumcised when I was eight days old. I am a pure-blooded
        citizen of Israel and a member of the tribe of Benjamin\u2014a real Hebrew
        if there ever was one! I was a member of the Pharisees, who demand the strictest
        obedience to the Jewish law. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I was so zealous that I harshly persecuted the church. And as for
        righteousness, I obeyed the law without fault.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I once thought these things were valuable, but now I consider them
        worthless because of what Christ has done. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, everything else is worthless when compared with the infinite
        value of knowing Christ Jesus my Lord. For his sake I have discarded everything
        else, counting it all as garbage, so that I could gain Christ '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "and become one with him. I no longer count on my own righteousness
        through obeying the law; rather, I become righteous through faith in Christ.[COMMENT[0]]
        For God\u2019s way of making us right with himself depends on faith. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:9 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: through the faithfulness of Christ.
    - title: 
      content: 'I want to know Christ and experience the mighty power that raised
        him from the dead. I want to suffer with him, sharing in his death, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so that one way or another I will experience the resurrection from
        the dead!  '
      comments: []
    - title: Pressing toward the Goal
      content: "I don\u2019t mean to say that I have already achieved these things
        or that I have already reached perfection. But I press on to possess that
        perfection for which Christ Jesus first possessed me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'No, dear brothers and sisters, I have not achieved it,[COMMENT[0]]
        but I focus on this one thing: Forgetting the past and looking forward to
        what lies ahead, '
      comments:
      - number: '3:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts read '
          body: not yet achieved it.
    - title: 
      content: 'I press on to reach the end of the race and receive the heavenly
        prize for which God, through Christ Jesus, is calling us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let all who are spiritually mature agree on these things. If you
        disagree on some point, I believe God will make it plain to you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But we must hold on to the progress we have already made.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters, pattern your lives after mine, and learn
        from those who follow our example. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I have told you often before, and I say it again with tears in
        my eyes, that there are many whose conduct shows they are really enemies
        of the cross of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They are headed for destruction. Their god is their appetite, they
        brag about shameful things, and they think only about this life here on earth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But we are citizens of heaven, where the Lord Jesus Christ lives.
        And we are eagerly waiting for him to return as our Savior. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: He will take our weak mortal bodies and change them into glorious
        bodies like his own, using the same power with which he will bring everything
        under his control.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: 'Therefore, my dear brothers and sisters,[COMMENT[0]] stay true to
        the Lord. I love you and long to see you, dear friends, for you are my joy
        and the crown I receive for my work.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: 'brothers; '
        - ft: also in 4:8.
          body: 
    - title: Words of Encouragement
      content: 'Now I appeal to Euodia and Syntyche. Please, because you belong to
        the Lord, settle your disagreement. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And I ask you, my true partner,[COMMENT[0]] to help these two women,
        for they worked hard with me in telling others the Good News. They worked
        along with Clement and the rest of my co-workers, whose names are written
        in the Book of Life.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Or '
          body: loyal Syzygus.
    - title: 
      content: "Always be full of joy in the Lord. I say it again\u2014rejoice! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Let everyone see that you are considerate in all you do. Remember,
        the Lord is coming soon.[COMMENT[0]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:5 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: the Lord is near.
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t worry about anything; instead, pray about everything.
        Tell God what you need, and thank him for all he has done. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then you will experience God\u2019s peace, which exceeds anything
        we can understand. His peace will guard your hearts and minds as you live
        in Christ Jesus.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And now, dear brothers and sisters, one final thing. Fix your thoughts
        on what is true, and honorable, and right, and pure, and lovely, and admirable.
        Think about things that are excellent and worthy of praise. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Keep putting into practice all you learned and received from me\u2014everything
        you heard from me and saw me doing. Then the God of peace will be with you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Thanks for Their Gifts"
      content: "How I praise the Lord that you are concerned about me again. I know
        you have always been concerned for me, but you didn\u2019t have the chance
        to help me. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Not that I was ever in need, for I have learned how to be content
        with whatever I have. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I know how to live on almost nothing or with everything. I have learned
        the secret of living in every situation, whether it is with a full stomach
        or empty, with plenty or little. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I can do everything through Christ,[COMMENT[0]] who gives me
        strength. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Greek '
          body: through the one.
    - title: 
      content: 'Even so, you have done well to share with me in my present difficulty.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As you know, you Philippians were the only ones who gave me financial
        help when I first brought you the Good News and then traveled on from Macedonia.
        No other church did this. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even when I was in Thessalonica you sent help more than once. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I don\u2019t say this because I want a gift from you. Rather, I want
        you to receive a reward for your kindness.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "At the moment I have all I need\u2014and more! I am generously supplied
        with the gifts you sent me with Epaphroditus. They are a sweet-smelling sacrifice
        that is acceptable and pleasing to God. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And this same God who takes care of me will supply all your needs
        from his glorious riches, which have been given to us in Christ Jesus.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now all glory to God our Father forever and ever! Amen.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Greetings"
      content: "Give my greetings to each of God\u2019s holy people\u2014all who
        belong to Christ Jesus. The brothers who are with me send you their greetings. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And all the rest of God\u2019s people send you greetings, too, especially
        those in Caesar\u2019s household.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: May the grace of the Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit.[COMMENT[0]]
      comments:
      - number: '4:23 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Some manuscripts add '
          body: Amen.
